# UI_UX_Design

## 1. Applies when
UI is complex — multiple menus, inventory, skill tree, map, quest log, HUD.

## 2. This document owns
HUD; menus; information architecture; interaction flow; usability; feedback rules;
prompt system; accessibility.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Gameplay numbers behind widgets; store pricing (Monetization); narrative content.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. HUD · 3. Menus · 4. Information architecture ·
5. Interaction flow · 6. Feedback & prompts · 7. Accessibility · 8. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- UI vs Gameplay — presentation vs the numbers it shows.
- UI vs Store — game UI vs monetization storefront.
- UI vs Pipeline — HUD widgets vs narrative delivery rules.

## 6. Common audit rules
- UI references gameplay/economy values, does not own them.
- Store surfaces are separated from core UI.
